1.线性差分方程组的解的原理

具体见讲义，此处做一简单总结。

差分方程可以写成，

\[\Delta X_{t+1}=AX_t+b\]

或者展开成， \[X_{t+1}=(A+I)X_t+b=\hat{A}X_t+b\]

很显然，稳态解为， \[\bar{X}=-A^{-1}b\]

递归得到的解为， \[X_t=\hat{A}^t(X_0-\bar{X})+\bar{X}\]

2. 代码和图形

2.1 全局稳定系统

\[\begin{bmatrix}X_{1,t+1}\\X_{2,t+1}\end{bmatrix}=\begin{bmatrix}1&0\\0&1\end{bmatrix}\begin{bmatrix}0.8&0\\0&0.7\end{bmatrix}\begin{bmatrix}1&0\\0&1\end{bmatrix}\begin{bmatrix}X_{1t}\\X_{2t}\end{bmatrix}+\begin{bmatrix}1\\ 2\end{bmatrix}\]

注意上式使用了\(\hat{A}\)的特征值分解形式。先来生成\(A\)矩阵和\(b\)向量，同时随便赋一个初值\(X_0\)，

rm(list = ls())
library(matlab)
hatA <- matrix(c(1,0,0,1), nrow = 2) %*% diag(c(0.8,0.7)) %*% matrix(c(1,0,0,1), nrow = 2)
b <- matrix(c(1,2), ncol = 1)
X0 <- matrix(c(0,0), ncol = 1)
hatA
##      [,1] [,2]
## [1,]  0.8  0.0
## [2,]  0.0  0.7
b
##      [,1]
## [1,]    1
## [2,]    2
X0
##      [,1]
## [1,]    0
## [2,]    0

根据公式可以得到稳态解和递归的解，

Xbar <- -solve(hatA - eye(2)) %*% b
Xbar # 稳态
##          [,1]
## [1,] 5.000000
## [2,] 6.666667
Xt <- matrix(NA, nrow = 2, ncol = 30)
ans <- hatA
for (i in 1:ncol(Xt)) {
  Xt[,i] <- ans %*% (X0-Xbar)+Xbar
  ans <- ans %*% hatA
}
library(tidyverse)
Xt <- t(Xt) %>% as.data.frame()
Xt # 运动轨迹

2.2 鞍点稳定系统

\[\begin{bmatrix}X_{1,t+1}\\X_{2,t+1}\end{bmatrix}=\begin{bmatrix}1&0\\0&1\end{bmatrix}\begin{bmatrix}1.8&0\\0&0.7\end{bmatrix}\begin{bmatrix}1&0\\0&1\end{bmatrix}\begin{bmatrix}X_{1t}\\X_{2t}\end{bmatrix}+\begin{bmatrix}1\\ 2\end{bmatrix}\]

更改矩阵\(\hat{A}\)的设置，使得系统是鞍点稳定，

hatA <- matrix(c(1,0,0,1), nrow = 2) %*% diag(c(1.8,0.7)) %*% matrix(c(1,0,0,1), nrow = 2)
Xbar <- -solve(hatA - eye(2)) %*% b
Xt <- matrix(NA, nrow = 2, ncol = 20)
ans <- hatA
for (i in 1:ncol(Xt)) {
  Xt[,i] <- ans %*% (X0-Xbar)+Xbar
  ans <- ans %*% hatA
}
Xt <- t(Xt) %>% as.data.frame()
Xt$tm <- 1:nrow(Xt)
p1 <- ggplot(Xt, aes(x = tm, y = V1)) + geom_line() + labs(x = 'time',y = 'X1')
p2 <- ggplot(Xt, aes(x = tm, y = V2)) + geom_line(color = I('red')) + labs(x = 'time',y = 'X2')
library(patchwork)
p1+ p2

双变量还有一种相位图非常有用。相位图只是上图的另外一种表述，相位图的横纵坐标为\(X_1,X_2\)，

library(ggquiver)
expand.grid(x = seq(-25,25,4), y = seq(-25,25,4)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x,y,u=0.8*x+1,v = -0.3*y+2)) + geom_quiver() +
  geom_hline(yintercept = Xbar[2], color = I('red')) + labs(x = 'X1', y = 'X2') +
  geom_vline(xintercept = Xbar[1], color = I('blue'))

  • 可以看到所有点趋向红线，但在x轴上发散。
  • 但x轴的蓝线上是稳定的，这根线就是鞍点路径，只有在这条线上才能稳定，其他所有地方都是发散。

2.3 震荡发散和震荡稳定系统

\[\begin{bmatrix}X_{1,t+1}\\X_{2,t+1}\end{bmatrix}=\begin{bmatrix}1.5&1\\-1&0.6\end{bmatrix}\begin{bmatrix}X_{1t}\\X_{2t}\end{bmatrix}+\begin{bmatrix}1\\ 2\end{bmatrix}\]

我们这里构造一个特征值为复根的震荡发散的\(\hat{A}\)如下，

hatA <- matrix(c(1.5,-1,1,0.6), nrow = 2) 
eigen(hatA) # 特征值和特征向量
## eigen() decomposition
## $values
## [1] 1.05+0.893029i 1.05-0.893029i
## 
## $vectors
##                       [,1]                  [,2]
## [1,]  0.7071068+0.0000000i  0.7071068+0.0000000i
## [2,] -0.3181981+0.6314665i -0.3181981-0.6314665i
eigen(hatA) %>% .$values %>% Mod() # 特征值的模
## [1] 1.378405 1.378405

模大于1，可知必然发散。接下来计算系统随时间的运动轨迹，

Xbar <- -solve(hatA - eye(2)) %*% b
Xt <- matrix(NA, nrow = 2, ncol = 30)
ans <- hatA
for (n in 1:ncol(Xt)) {
  Xt[,n] <- ans %*% (X0-Xbar)+Xbar
  ans <- ans %*% hatA
}
Xt <- t(Xt) %>% as.data.frame()
Xt$tm <- 1:nrow(Xt)
ggplot(Xt, aes(x = tm, y = V1)) + geom_line() + geom_line(aes(y = V2), color = I('red')) + labs(x = 'time', y = 'X')

相位图如下，

expand.grid(x = seq(-25,25,4), y = seq(-25,25,4)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x,y,u=0.5*x+y+1,v = -x-0.4*y+2)) + geom_quiver()

构造一个特征值为复根的震荡稳定的系统如下， \[\begin{bmatrix}X_{1,t+1}\\X_{2,t+1}\end{bmatrix}=\begin{bmatrix}0&1\\-0.8&0.5\end{bmatrix}\begin{bmatrix}X_{1t}\\X_{2t}\end{bmatrix}+\begin{bmatrix}1\\ 2\end{bmatrix}\]

hatA <- matrix(c(0,-0.8,1,0.5), nrow = 2) 
eigen(hatA) # 特征值和特征向量
## eigen() decomposition
## $values
## [1] 0.25+0.8587782i 0.25-0.8587782i
## 
## $vectors
##                     [,1]                [,2]
## [1,] 0.745356+0.0000000i 0.745356+0.0000000i
## [2,] 0.186339+0.6400955i 0.186339-0.6400955i
eigen(hatA) %>% .$values %>% Mod() # 特征值的模
## [1] 0.8944272 0.8944272

绘制时间轨迹，

Xbar <- -solve(hatA - eye(2)) %*% b
Xt <- matrix(NA, nrow = 2, ncol = 30)
ans <- hatA
for (n in 1:ncol(Xt)) {
  Xt[,n] <- ans %*% (X0-Xbar)+Xbar
  ans <- ans %*% hatA
}
Xt <- t(Xt) %>% as.data.frame()
Xt$tm <- 1:nrow(Xt)
p1 <- ggplot(Xt, aes(x = tm, y = V1)) + geom_line() + labs(x = 'time',y = 'X1')
p2 <- ggplot(Xt, aes(x = tm, y = V2)) + geom_line(color = I('red')) + labs(x = 'time',y = 'X2')
library(patchwork)
p1+ p2                                                            

expand.grid(x = seq(-25,25,4), y = seq(-25,25,4)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x,y,u=-x+y+1,v = -0.8*x-0.5*y+2)) + geom_quiver() +
  geom_point(aes(x = Xbar[1], y = Xbar[2]), size = 5, color = I('red'), shape = 1)
